{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782750817214,"sessionID":"ses_0ebcbd824ffeY6bdd3Qgc3G0aZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_a6e4ef2923c24ebebae30b14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd .opencode/skills/sk-design && rg -n --no-heading -e '\\b[0-9]{3}-[a-z]' -e 'spec[s]?/[0-9]{3}' -e 'packet' -e 'phase-[0-9]' -e 'ADR-[0-9]' -e 'REQ-[0-9]' -e 'T[0-9]{3}' --glob '!**/node_modules/**' --glob '!**/changelog/**' --glob '!**/*.json' 2>&1 | head -40","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"SKILL.md:15:One skill, five design modes, one shared reference base. `sk-design` is the public, advisor-routable home for every design persona; the shared design reference base (anti-slop principles, cognitive laws, design-token vocabulary) is the common vocabulary the modes cite. This hub holds NO per-mode design logic — each mode keeps its own contract in its packet, and the hub only routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`.\nSKILL.md:21:Use this skill (through the hub) for any design-family workflow. Invoke it as `sk-design` (optionally with a mode hint such as `motion: <request>`); the hub classifies the request, resolves a mode key, and loads the matching nested packet.\nSKILL.md:52:  → load the mode packet at registry[mode].packet (e.g. sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md)\nSKILL.md:62:Per-mode behavior is **not flattened**: each packet keeps its own design judgment, examples, standards, verification, and tool-permission needs. The four doc-guidance modes are read-and-guide; `md-generator` is the only mode that runs an extraction pipeline (Write/Edit/Bash over Playwright).\nSKILL.md:75:  design-interface/  design-foundations/  design-motion/  design-audit/  design-md-generator/   # five mode packets\nSKILL.md:78:Each mode packet is self-contained (its own `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, and `md-generator`'s extraction backend), with internal paths repointed and **no per-packet `graph-metadata.json`** — only this hub carries one, so the advisor discovers exactly one skill. The mode packet folders are created when the flat skills move under the hub; the hub references those packet paths now.\nSKILL.md:89:- **ALWAYS** keep each mode's design judgment, examples, and verification in its packet — the hub stays logic-free.\nSKILL.md:91:- **ALWAYS** give every mode an `advisorRouting` block with a valid `routingClass` and `packetSkillName`.\nSKILL.md:95:- **NEVER** add a `graph-metadata.json` or a discoverable skill marker inside a mode packet or the shared reference base.\nSKILL.md:96:- **NEVER** embed per-mode design instructions in this hub — that content lives in the packets.\nSKILL.md:101:- A new design mode is needed — extend `mode-registry.json` and open a packet; do not bolt logic onto the hub.\nSKILL.md:110:- Mode packets: `design-interface/SKILL.md`, `design-foundations/SKILL.md`, `design-motion/SKILL.md`, `design-audit/SKILL.md`, `design-md-generator/SKILL.md` (per-mode detail).\nSKILL.md:119:- The selected mode packet owns the detailed design workflow; the hub stayed routing-only.\nSKILL.md:121:- Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` exists for the whole skill; no packet carries its own.\nSKILL.md:143:- Pattern: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation/parent_skills_nested_packets.md` (parent-skill hub + nested packets, the one-graph-metadata invariant).\nSKILL.md:144:- Canonical example: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/` (hub + `mode-registry.json` + mode packets).\nREADME.md:70:The mode packets carry no `graph-metadata.json` of their own, so the advisor discovers exactly one design skill. The shared baselines under `shared/` (anti-slop principles, cognitive laws and the design-token vocabulary) load for every mode.\nREADME.md:95:| [`mode-registry.json`](./mode-registry.json) | The mode-to-packet routing map. |\nREADME.md:96:| [`design-interface/SKILL.md`](./design-interface/SKILL.md) | An example mode packet. |\ndesign-motion/README.md:50:**Run the restraint gate.** `references/animation_decision_framework.md` runs four checks in order and stops at the first no. Frequency: a 100-plus-times-a-day action is never animated. Input: a keyboard-driven action stays instant. Purpose: name one reason from feedback, orientation, focus, continuity, perceived performance or earned delight. Register: confirm the choice fits the budget dial.\ndesign-md-generator/README.md:47:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/extract.ts https://stripe.com --fast --output .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output\ndesign-md-generator/README.md:56:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts DESIGN.md .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json\ndesign-md-generator/README.md:114:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/extract.ts <url> [options] --output .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output\ndesign-interface/SKILL.md:90:The Resource Loading Levels table above is the human-readable view; the fenced block below is the machine-parseable router that drives deterministic routing and the skill-benchmark D5 connectivity gate. `INTENT_SIGNALS` scores the lowercased task by keyword, `RESOURCE_MAP` maps each intent to the in-skill references and assets it loads, and `DEFAULT_RESOURCE` is loaded on every design task. Routing semantics match the table one-for-one: the same references load for the same intents. The shared register (`../shared/register.md`) is loaded on every task via `DEFAULT_RESOURCE`. It lives in the parent skill's `shared/` dir, a sanctioned cross-packet location the D5 gate recognizes.\ndesign-interface/SKILL.md:281:The router (Section 2) loads `references/design-process/design_principles.md` for every design task. Hand implementation to `sk-code`, use `mcp-chrome-devtools` for screenshot-based self-critique, and reach for `system-spec-kit` when the work needs packet documentation.\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:298:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/extract.ts <url> --fast --output .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:303:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/build-write-prompt.ts .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:306:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts <DESIGN.md> .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:309:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/proof.ts <url> .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:310:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/report-gen.ts .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json <dir> <DESIGN.md>\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:311:npx ts-node .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/preview-gen.ts .opencode/specs/<track>/<packet>/output/tokens.json <dir>\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:447:- **`system-spec-kit`** applies when the extraction is part of a larger spec-tracked feature and packet documentation is required.\ndesign-md-generator/SKILL.md:469:Related skills: `interface` (the design-judgment sibling — invents new direction, consumes DESIGN.md as ground truth), `sk-code` (consumes DESIGN.md as the implementation contract), `mcp-figma` (extracts from Figma Desktop, not live URLs), `mcp-open-design` (extracts from Open Design projects), `mcp-chrome-devtools` (for browser inspection and visual preview, not structured extraction), and `system-spec-kit` when the extraction is part of a tracked packet.\ndesign-foundations/SKILL.md:144:    # sanctioned cross-packet location. Every other parent path is rejected.\ndesign-motion/SKILL.md:160:    # sanctioned cross-packet location. Every other parent path is rejected.\nshared/sk_code_handoff.md:16: